<paragraph id="725E36EC2446BD1FFF66DEDA1AC9A3FE" blockId="88.[151,1437,152,642]" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis id="4095EAFE2446BD1FFF66DEDA1AFFA3B3" bold="true" box="[198,448,152,178]" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">Taxonomic notes:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="B5E14D6F2446BD1FFE61DEDA19FCA3B3" authorityName="Trail" authorityYear="1876" box="[449,707,152,178]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="88" pageNumber="89" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="leptospadix">
<emphasis id="4095EAFE2446BD1FFE61DEDA19FCA3B3" box="[449,707,152,178]" italics="true" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">Geonoma leptospadix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears similar to both 
<taxonomicName id="B5E14D6F2446BD1FFC45DEDA1F61A3B3" authorityName="Kunth" authorityYear="1841" baseAuthorityName="Poiteau" box="[997,1118,152,178]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="88" pageNumber="89" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="deversa">
<emphasis id="4095EAFE2446BD1FFC45DEDA1F61A3B3" box="[997,1118,152,178]" italics="true" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">G. deversa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="B5E14D6F2446BD1FFB3EDEDA1E1AA3B3" authorityName="Martius" authorityYear="1823" box="[1182,1317,152,178]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="88" pageNumber="89" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="laxiflora">
<emphasis id="4095EAFE2446BD1FFB3EDEDA1E1AA3B3" box="[1182,1317,152,178]" italics="true" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">G. laxiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="B5E14D6F2446BD1FFF78DEFC1A6AA3D9" authorityName="Kunth" authorityYear="1841" baseAuthorityName="Poiteau" box="[216,341,190,216]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="88" pageNumber="89" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="deversa">
<emphasis id="4095EAFE2446BD1FFF78DEFC1A6AA3D9" box="[216,341,190,216]" italics="true" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">G. deversa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its spirally arranged flower pits and from 
<taxonomicName id="B5E14D6F2446BD1FFCCDDEFC18CBA3D9" authorityName="Martius" authorityYear="1823" box="[877,1012,190,216]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="88" pageNumber="89" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="laxiflora">
<emphasis id="4095EAFE2446BD1FFCCDDEFC18CBA3D9" box="[877,1012,190,216]" italics="true" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">G. laxiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its prophylls which are not short and asymmetrically apiculate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="725E36EC2446BD1FFF66DF4E194EA24D" blockId="88.[151,1437,152,642]" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis id="4095EAFE2446BD1FFF66DF4E1ACAA227" bold="true" box="[198,501,268,294]" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">Subspecific variation:—</emphasis>
No trait varies within this species except for stem branching and leaf division. One specimen (of 47) has a pinnate leaf.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="725E36EC2446BD1FFF66DF1B19A5A15A" blockId="88.[151,1437,152,642]" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">
There is geographical variation in this species. Regression shows there are significant associations between longitude and two stem, six leaf and four inflorescence variables. Squared multiple 
<emphasis id="4095EAFE2446BD1FFA8CDFC31E00A29B" box="[1324,1343,385,410]" italics="true" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">R</emphasis>
for the regression of plant height on longitude is 0.15, stem diameter 0.43, petiole length 0.24, rachis length 0.37, rachis width 0.23, basal pinna angle 0.08, apical pinna length 0.29, apical pinna angle 0.25, prophyll length 0.45, peduncle length 0.43, peduncle width 0.14, and rachillae length 0.38. From east to west, plants become taller with thinner stems, petioles longer, and basal and apical angles wider. All other variables decrease and inflorescences in particular become smaller.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="725E36EC2446BD1FFF66DC2A1F41A183" blockId="88.[151,1437,152,642]" box="[198,1150,616,642]" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">
See under 
<taxonomicName id="B5E14D6F2446BD1FFEE2DC2A1929A183" authorityName="Kunth" authorityYear="1841" baseAuthorityName="Poiteau" box="[322,534,616,642]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="88" pageNumber="89" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="deversa">
<emphasis id="4095EAFE2446BD1FFEE2DC2A1929A183" box="[322,534,616,642]" italics="true" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">Geonoma deversa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for hybrids between that species and 
<taxonomicName id="B5E14D6F2446BD1FFC70DC2A1F48A183" authorityName="Trail" authorityYear="1876" box="[976,1143,616,642]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="88" pageNumber="89" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="leptospadix">
<emphasis id="4095EAFE2446BD1FFC70DC2A1F48A183" box="[976,1143,616,642]" italics="true" pageId="88" pageNumber="89">G. leptospadix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
